Sheet 5 — Top 10 Rankings
Use LARGE + RANK per month/market:
=RANK(F2, IF(($A$2:$A$200=A2)*($B$2:$B$200=B2), $F$2:$F$200), 0)
(Enter as Ctrl+Shift+Enter array formula, or use RANKX in Power Pivot)
Then filter: rank <= 10 using AutoFilter or a slicer on a formatted Table.
